  "bib_entries": {
    "32770429": {
      "title": "A hybrid 3D image registration of lung CT images for respiration",
      "abstract": "In order to model the respiration motion, compensate the error of image-guided computer aided surgery system, we need to calculate the 3D transformation between end-inhalation frame and end-exhalation frame. We proposed and realized a 3D image registration approach which could better fit for the respiration motion in lungs. According to the flexibility of human body, we designed a registration approach which combines two image registration approaches. One is the 3D affine registration which can model the motion of the whole body such as twisting, stretching and shifting. The other is the 3D multi-resolution b-spline non-rigid registration which can model the local motion in the organs. The two registration approaches work together can extract more precise 3D transformations. The experiment results proved that the error of this approach had reached the sub-voxel level, which means the error is smaller than 2mm, thus it could meet the needs of clinical applications."
    }
  },
